Cord and Kanu leaders flocked the thanksgiving rally for Bomet governor Isaac Rutto on Sunday.The meeting was organised to welcome the governor after he jetted back into the country from South Africa on Saturday.Rutto left for SA two weeks ago for specialised treatment of his eye that was injured after he was hit by a teargas canister.Wiper party leader Kalonzo Musyoka, Amani leader Musalia Mudavadi and governors Jack Ranguma (Kisumu), Wycliffe Oparanya (Kakamega) attended the meeting.Baringo Senator Gideon Moi, MPs John Mbadi (Gwassi), Zakayo Cheruiyot (Kuresoi South), Johanna Ngeno (Emurua Dikirr) and Kanu secretary general Nick Salat were present.Bomet governor Isaac Rutto accompanied by leaders during his homecoming rally on Sunday. /FELIX KIPKEMOIThe meeting was expected to attract more than 30,000 people in what has been perceived as signaling the birth of national super alliance (NASA).Read: Rutto Bomet rally to launch Super AllianceRutto received a hero's welcome at the JKIA on Friday. Read: Hero's welcome awaits Rutto on arrival from South AfricaAccompanied by MP Cheruiyot, he thanked Kenyans for praying for him and cracked a few jokes, making light of the injury he suffered near his right eye.He was injured during a fracas between his supporters and those of National Assembly Deputy Speaker Joyce Laboso at Silibwet in Bomet Central during a football match between Bunge FC and Bomet-based Silibwet FC.Read: Hundreds line up on Narok-Bomet highway to welcome Rutto from SARutto said that he has forgiven the Administration Police officer who allegedly lobbed a teargas canister and injured him at Silibwet on November 6.Kanu Secretary General Nick Salat with Baringo senator Gideon Moi wave at hundreds of residents atop their vehicle as they arrive at the Bomet stadium on Sunday. /FELIX KIPKEMOI